'''Drive-through road stops''' ('''DTRS''') make available a new kind of [[en/Manual/Stations|station]] for [[en/Manual/Road vehicles]].  Much like a traditional real-life "bus stop", these new stations allow road vehicles to load/unload passengers and [[en/Manual/Cargo|cargo]] simply by stopping by the side of the road, then continue along the road out the other side of the station.  These stations greatly increase the efficiency of road vehicles.

By default, a DTRS must be built either on an open plot of land, or on a stretch of road currently owned by the player.  However, you can enable the building of a drive-through on a town-owned road by setting the '''Stations/Allow drive-through road stops on town-owned roads''' patch to '''On''' within the [[en/Archive/Manual/Settings/Configuring patches/Stations|Configure Patches - Stations]] menu.  When a stop is built on a township road, ownership of the road itself remains with the township.  DTRS can never be built on a road owned by an opponent.


