#Open the road station menu as normal
#Click on the drive-through graphic[[File:en/Manual/DriveThru Menu.gif|none]]
#Either find an open plot of land, or find an existing stretch of road to build the station on[[File:en/Manual/DriveThru Placement.gif|none]]

==Other notes on DTRS==
[[File:en/Manual/DriveThru Multiple.gif|frame|Sequenced Drive-throughs allow for efficient handling of multiple vehicles]]
*Opponents' vehicles can go through your drive-through stops without stopping (and your vehicles can go through theirs).
*Using the dynamite tool on a DTRS will remove both the station and the road, if you are allowed to remove the road. If not, the dynamite button will do nothing.  Using the remove/bulldoze tool will remove only the station and leave the road.
*If a DTRS is connected to a road on only end (rather than both), the stop will behave like a default station (i.e. the vehicle will turn around to exit the stop.)
*If not scheduled to stop at a given DTRS, road vehicles will try to avoid driving through them if an alternate route is available.
*Several stations can be built in sequence, and road vehicles arriving at the station will automatically load at the furthest open location, leaving nearer stations open to later-arriving vehicles
*DTRS are available from [[en/Archive/Community/Nightly build]] r8735 on. They are not yet available in any release version, but are planned for inclusion in [[en/Archive/Lists/Roadmap 0.6|next version]].

